      [1;34m"body"[m[1;37m:[m [32m"### PR Summary:\nThis PR introduces a Flask-based web application (`app.py`) serving as a landing/download site for Package Maker. Key additions:\n- Platform-aware download page (Android/Windows/Linux detection via User-Agent)\n- SQLite-backed visit analytics with a `/admin/stats` dashboard\n- GitHub Releases API integration to surface available `.iflapp` downloads\n- PWA support (service worker, manifest)\n- Removal of the old `updater.py` PyQt6 desktop updater\n\n### Review Summary:\nThe platform detection logic and download page UI are well-structured and the Jinja2 templating is clean. However, the PR introduces several security and reliability issues that need to be addressed before merging.\n\n**Security concerns are the most pressing:** the Flask secret key is hardcoded in source, and the `/admin/stats` endpoint (which exposes visitor IPs and session metadata) has absolutely no authentication guard.\n\n**Reliability:** Every `/download` page render chains two synchronous, uncached HTTP calls to GitHub (API fetch + HEAD existence check with a 10 s timeout), which will cause significant latency and occasional timeouts in production.\n\n**Bug:** The `UPDATE visits ... ORDER BY id DESC LIMIT 1` SQL is invalid in standard SQLite builds, silently swallowing all bounce/duration updates via a bare `except: pass`.\n\nThe `lib/config.py` already has the right pattern (`os.environ.get(...)`) for secrets but `app.py` doesn't use it — wiring these together would resolve comment #1.\n\n### Suggestions\n- Add a TTL-based in-memory cache (e.g. 5-minute expiry) for `get_release_info()` and remove the `check_iflapp_exists()` synchronous HEAD call to eliminate per-request GitHub latency. **[Apply](https://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?client_id=Ov23liSHXo8N3GjkyDT7&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fdevlo.ai%2Fauth%2Fgithub&state=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJkZXZsby1hcGkiLCJhdWQiOiJnaXRodWItYXV0aC1kZXZsby1tdWx0aSIsInR5cGUiOiJhY3Rpb25MaW5rIiwicmVwb0lkIjoiMTAzNDY1NDYyMiIsInB1bGxOdW1iZXIiOiIzIiwibGlua0lkIjoiNDUxOTFkNzQtNjY2ZS00Mjc5LWEyMmQtNzMwYTgyYWVjYzBkIiwibGlua1R5cGUiOiJzdWdnZXN0aW9uX2ZpeCIsImV4cCI6MTc4MzcwNDAzMn0.HdPexgldontYrsBFO8KRL279rtO83_USiIYCr96sVsU&scope=read%3Auser+user%3Aemail)**\n- Wire `app.py` to use the existing `lib/config.py` `Config` class so secrets (`SECRET_KEY`) and settings are managed from environment variables consistently. **[Apply](https://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?client_id=Ov23liSHXo8N3GjkyDT7&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fdevlo.ai%2Fauth%2Fgithub&state=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJkZXZsby1hcGkiLCJhdWQiOiJnaXRodWItYXV0aC1kZXZsby1tdWx0aSIsInR5cGUiOiJhY3Rpb25MaW5rIiwicmVwb0lkIjoiMTAzNDY1NDYyMiIsInB1bGxOdW1iZXIiOiIzIiwibGlua0lkIjoiNmQ0YzEyOWMtMWQwYi00ZTI3LTk4ZmMtMDMzMGU3ZjdhYzAwIiwibGlua1R5cGUiOiJzdWdnZXN0aW9uX2ZpeCIsImV4cCI6MTc4MzcwNDAzMn0._GZEDLcW6SG0MMFytvV5Bs7GxskWoyM0IB6zsAIZ_j4&scope=read%3Auser+user%3Aemail)**\n\n\n---\n⚡ **[Apply all quick fixes](https://github.com/login/oauth/authorize?client_id=Ov23liSHXo8N3GjkyDT7&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fdevlo.ai%2Fauth%2Fgithub&state=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJkZXZsby1hcGkiLCJhdWQiOiJnaXRodWItYXV0aC1kZXZsby1tdWx0aSIsInR5cGUiOiJhY3Rpb25MaW5rIiwicmVwb0lkIjoiMTAzNDY1NDYyMiIsInB1bGxOdW1iZXIiOiIzIiwibGlua0lkIjoiMWUwNDY1YjQtODY4Yi00NGQyLTk1MjMtMjYyNzEzMWYxYWM1IiwibGlua1R5cGUiOiJmaXhfYWxsIiwiZXhwIjoxNzgzNzA0MDMyfQ.zOhmQOQqyBmFu9uYeSyK3uu1RB3SPS2XKblDNE1VRq8&scope=read%3Auser+user%3Aemail)** (5 quick fixes)"[m[1;37m,[m
